.TH minios-kernel 1 "August 2025" "MiniOS Linux" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
minios-kernel \- Command-line tool for managing MiniOS kernels
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B minios-kernel
.BR list " [" --json ]
.br
.B minios-kernel
.BR activate " " <kernel-version> " [" --json ]
.br
.B minios-kernel
.BR info " [" <kernel-version> "] [" --json ]
.br
.B minios-kernel
.BR package " {" --repo " " <package> " | " --deb " " <file> "} " -o " " <output-dir> " [options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B minios-kernel
is a command-line utility for managing Linux kernels in the MiniOS distribution. It provides commands for listing, activating, and packaging kernels, with JSON output support for GUI integration.
.PP
This tool serves as both a standalone CLI utility and the backend for the graphical
.BR minios-kernel-manager .
It handles kernel packaging, activation, and provides detailed kernel information.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BR list " [" --json ]
List available kernels with their status. Shows active kernel and available kernels in the repository.
.TP
.BR activate " " <kernel-version> " [" --json ]
Activate the specified kernel version for the next boot. Updates bootloader configuration and kernel symlinks.
.TP
.BR info " [" <kernel-version> "] [" --json ]
Show detailed information about a kernel. If no version is specified, shows information about the currently active kernel.
.TP
.BR package " " <source> " " -o " " <output-dir> " [options]
Package a kernel from repository or local .deb file. Creates SquashFS image, initramfs, and copies kernel files.
.SH PACKAGE OPTIONS
.TP
.BR --repo " " <package-name>
Download and package kernel from APT repository (e.g., \fIlinux-image-6.12.38+deb13-rt-amd64\fR).
.TP
.BR --deb " " <deb-file>
Package kernel from local .deb file.
.TP
.BR -o ", " --output " " <output-dir>
Directory to save packaged kernel files (vmlinuz, initrfs, SquashFS module). Required for package command.
.TP
.BR --sqfs-comp " " <compression>
Compression method for SquashFS image. Default: \fBzstd\fR. Options: \fBgzip\fR, \fBlz4\fR, \fBxz\fR, \fBzstd\fR.
.TP
.BR --init-comp " " <compression>
Compression method for initramfs. Default: \fBzstd\fR. Options: \fBgzip\fR, \fBlz4\fR, \fBxz\fR, \fBzstd\fR.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR --json
Output results in JSON format. Useful for GUI integration and scripting. Can be used with any command.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
List available kernels:
.B minios-kernel list
.TP
List kernels in JSON format:
.B minios-kernel --json list
.TP
Activate a specific kernel:
.B minios-kernel activate 6.12.38+deb13-amd64
.TP
Show current kernel information:
.B minios-kernel info
.TP
Package kernel from repository:
.B minios-kernel package --repo linux-image-6.12.38+deb13-rt-amd64 -o /tmp/output
.TP
Package from local .deb with custom compression:
.B minios-kernel package --deb /path/to/kernel.deb -o /tmp/output --sqfs-comp lz4
.SH JSON OUTPUT
When \fB--json\fR flag is used, commands return structured JSON data:
.TP
.B list
Returns array of kernels with version, status, and metadata.
.TP
.B activate
Returns success status and activation details.
.TP
.B info
Returns kernel information including version, status, and system paths.
.TP
.B package
Returns progress updates during packaging and final success status.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /run/initramfs/memory/data/minios/
Default MiniOS directory containing kernel files and configuration.
.TP
.I /minios/kernels/{version}/
Repository for inactive packaged kernels.
.TP
.I /minios/boot/vmlinuz-*
Active kernel image.
.TP
.I /minios/boot/initrfs-*.img
Active initramfs image.
.TP
.I /minios/01-kernel-*.sb
Active SquashFS kernel modules.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error (invalid arguments, kernel not found, etc.)
